text:
It looks like you have an Astro file (`index.astro`) with a basic setup for a homepage layout. You've imported a `HomepageLayout` component from your layouts directory and passed it some SEO data (title and description) as props. However, the body of your `` component is currently commented out, so no content would be visible on the page, only the layout provided by `HomepageLayout` and the SEO tags from the `seo` props would be applied. If you intend to display some content, you should include it within the `` tags. For example: ```jsx

Welcome to Roos Evers Holistic Skincare

Explore our range of natural skincare products and dive into a world of purity and wellness.

 ``` This example adds a heading and a paragraph inside your `HomepageLayout` component, which will be displayed on your homepage. You can replace or expand upon this content with whatever you need for your website.
summary: Adding content to HomepageLayout in Astro file
